Warm wishes from NSS family!<br>
<br>
NSS IITM joins hands with Ability Foundation, Chennai&nbsp;to bring to you =
the first skill development workshop of the semester:
<strong>Sign Language Workshop</strong>. Sign language is a language which =
chiefly uses manual communication to convey meaning. This involves hand sha=
pes, orientation and movement of hands, arms or body and facial expressions=
 to express a speaker's thoughts<span style=3D"font-size: 10pt;">.</span>
<div>
<div><br>
Ability Foundation is involved in pioneering activities, ranging from publi=
shing and media, counselling and referral services, advocacy, and training =
and employment. Over the years, the Foundation has organized several events=
 all of which aim at dispelling
 stereotypes and changing public attitudes/perceptions towards disabled per=
sons. Find more about Ability Foundation at&nbsp;
<a href=3D"http://www.abilityfoundation.org/" target=3D"_blank">http://www.=
abilityfoundation.org/</a><br>
